song_name: Long Way Home Live In The Country

version_description: Very basic chords and an easy strum pattern.
Goes right along with the song, be sure to get the hammer on pull of lick down. key change is easy just 1step up for last parts of song.
Where chords are written in a string (ex. G Am G) play a single strum like a step climb.
This is the Dan Fogelberg version. Chord changes are different from the original by the Cascades.
Basic chords, not as easy to pull from the piano.
Transcribed from the album Portrait: The Music of Dan Fogelberg.
